theorem Topology.interior_closure_eq_closure_inter_interior_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (A : Set X)) =
      closure (interior A) ∩ interior (closure (A : Set X)) := by
  -- We first show the inclusion from left to right.
  have h₁ :
      interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆
        closure (interior A) ∩ interior (closure (A : Set X)) := by
    intro x hx
    have hx₁ :
        x ∈ closure (interior A) :=
      (Topology.interior_closure_subset_closure_interior (A := A)) hx
    -- Assemble the two required facts.
    exact And.intro hx₁ hx
  -- The reverse inclusion is immediate from the definition of `∩`.
  have h₂ :
      closure (interior A) ∩ interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆
        interior (closure (A : Set X)) := by
    intro x hx
    exact hx.2
  -- Combine the two inclusions to obtain the desired equality.
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem Topology.interior_closure_subset_closure_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A → interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
  intro hP1
  exact Topology.interior_closure_subset_closure_interior_of_P1 (A := A) hP1
